cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper combines ideas from generative models and neural networks for the processing of graph data, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of deep architectures and probabilistic models also points towards cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of discriminative models, which could suggest cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with graph data, which could suggest cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
